           Fellowships   A fellow is the highest elected grade of membership in professional societies. Those elected as fellows are chosen by their peers in recognition of exceptional achievements and long-term contributions to the profession.      American Association for the Advancement of Science         names    2019: Isabel Cruz  2012: Suresh K. Aggarwal  2009: Ouri E. Wolfson  2006: Prith Banerjee, Gyungho Lee  2002: Mitra Dutta  2000: Lawrence A. Kennedy  1999: Michael A. Stroscio  1997: Jeffrey J.P. Tsai  1995: Thomas T.C. Ting  1990: Gyan C. Agarwal  1989: James C. Lin  1978: Wai-Kai Chen         American Concrete Institute International         names    1999: Mohsen A. Issa         American Institute for Medical and Biological Engineering         names    2019: Xincheng Yao  2017: Tom Royston, Michael Stroscio  2016: Eben Alsberg  2008: Jie Liang  2001: Richard Magin  1992: Gyan C. Agarwal, James C. Lin (founding members)         American Institute of Aeronautics and Astronautics         names    2002: Farzad Mashayek  1999: Lawrence A. Kennedy, Constantine M. Megaridis  1991: Suresh K. Aggarwal         American Institute of Chemical Engineers         names    1995: G. Ali Mansoori         American Physical Society         names    2016: Alexander Yarin  2011: Constantine M. Megaridis  2004: Michael A. Stroscio  2002: Lawrence A. Kennedy         American Society for Metals International         names    2003: J. Ernesto Indacochea  1998: Michael J. McNallan         American Society of Civil Engineers         names    2017: Hossein Ataei  2016: Mustafa Mahamid  2012: Krishna Reddy  2007: Mohsen A. Issa         American Society of Mechanical Engineers         names    2007: Thomas J. Royston  2006: Farzad Mashayek  2005: Suresh K. Aggarwal, Sabri Cetin  2003: Prashant Banerjee, Constantine M. Megaridis  1996: Ahmed A. Shabana  1993: Krishna Gupta  1992: Faydor Litvin  1986: W.J. Minkowycz, Chien H. Wu  1985: Thomas T.C. Ting  1984: Lawrence Kennedy         